Question: An array A consists of n integers in locations A[0], A[1]...A[n-1]. It is required to shift the elements of the array cyclically to the left by k places, where 1 <= k <= (n-1). Complete the algorithm by filling in the blanks.
min = n; i = 0;
while (__________) {
 temp = A[i]; j = i;
 while (__________) {
   A[j] = __________;
   j = (j + k) mod n;
   If (j < min) then min = j;
}
A[(n + i - k) mod n] = __________;
i = __________;
Options:
Choices:
a) i > min; j!= (n+i)mod n; A[j + k]; temp; i + 1 ;
b) i < min; j!= (n+i)mod n; A[j + k]; temp; i + 1;
c) i > min; j!= (n+i+k)mod n; A[(j + k)]; temp; i + 1;
d) i < min; j!= (n+i-k)mod n; A[(j + k)mod n]; temp; i + 1;
Answer: d

